@rabbah you aware of the risk with this change, opens the door for an user to forget that it configured the ~/.wskprops to allow insecure connections, and then use the file when it switches to interact with a production system with secure properly configured.?

Just want to hear if you did something to help the user in this case, like printing annoying message when using insecure, or other means.

We can merge this feature with the risk in place, just want to be sure you are OK with the security exposure.

@dubeejw did you squashed with new content?

It makes it difficult to review and see what's the delta from the last time you got a review.

Leave the previous commits as you make changes just add more commits, we will take care of squashing at the time of merging.

